<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#000000"><FONT color="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;Subject:&nbsp;Are you tired of being disconnected from Everquest</font></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" width="100%" valign="top"><tt><font color="#000000">
Author:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:&#107;&#121;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#108;&#108;&#101;&#64;&#106;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#105;&#99;&#101;&#100;&#101;&#97;&#114;&#100;&#111;&#114;&#46;&#122;&#122;&#110;&#46;&#99;&#111;&#109;?subject=Are you tired of being disconnected from Everquest">Kyrielle Iconoclast</a>&nbsp;(mango.arctic.net)<br>
Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10-19-2001 05:48<br><br>
Dear Everquest Player,<BR>
<BR>
Are you tired of being disconnected from Everquest and taken to the server screen when you either zone or die? Then you like hundred of others have a legitimate complaint against Verant. While Verant is spending all its time and money on the new expansion Shadows of Luclin, we the players are basically being given the run around over and over. Tech support tells us its an issue with our own machines. They offer no way to fix it. Reinstalling does not fix it. Rerunning the patches does not fix it. Reinstalling video drivers, sound drivers and Direct X does not fix it. Updating these drivers does not fix it either. And in game GM’s can offer no assistance, they claim that only technical support can fix this problem. And they have no record of this problem even existing.<BR>
<BR>
If you’ll notice this problem has only been happening since Server Side Filtering has been initiated. There is obviously some sort of bug. Yet no one is taking the time to fix this harassment. That is what I view it as, harassment.<BR>
<BR>
I am starting a campaign to get Verant to wake up and see this as a genuine problem. That it’s not just affecting a few people. It is affecting hundreds of people. <BR>
<BR>
If you wish to take part in this campaign please copy the following letter and send it to techsupport@everquest.com They will be forced to “open a ticket” for each e-mail they receive. It can no longer be ignored when this happens. So please take the time to help yourself and your fellow players who are always getting “booted” when they zone, losing their group and taking up time that is valuable to us all.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Dear Tech Support,<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
                For months now, I have been getting disconnected from Everquest and sent to the Server Screen when I zone, or die. I have tried re-installing Everquest, the Everquest patches, Direct X 8, and all my video and sound card drivers are completely up to date. I am requesting that a ticket be opened, and not closed until this problem is resolved. I, along with hundreds of other players have put up with this problem for months now and we would like to see it fixed. As a paying customer I feel this is my right. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Sincerely,<BR>
<BR>
(Enter your name here)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Feel free to reword this letter, or to send your own. It will only take a few moments for you to send this letter off, and hopefully Verant will get to the bottom of this issue and make it one of the top priorities to be fixed. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Thank you for your support,<BR>
<BR>
Kyrielle Iconoclast<BR>
Cleric of Tunare<BR>
Officer of Justice de`Ardor on the Veeshan Server<BR>
</font></tt></td>
</tr>
